ignition-tools
------------------------------------------
Ignition tools provide the ign command line tool that accepts multiple
subcommands. Each subcommand is implemented in a plugin that belongs to a
specific Ignition project. For example, all the commands that start with ign
topic ... will be implemented by the Ignition Transport library.

Runtime requirements:
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1
  ruby-2.3.6-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.31.0-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-5
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-5
  make-4.2.1-2
  ninja-1.8.2-2
  python-2.7.14-1
  ruby-2.3.6-1

Canonical website:
  https://ignitionrobotics.org/libraries/tools

Canonical download:
  https://bitbucket.org/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/get/ignition-tools_0.1.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ignition-tools-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ignition-tools-0.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ignition-tools-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ignition-tools-0.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ignition-tools)
  /usr/bin/ign
  /usr/lib/cmake/ignition-tools/ignition-tools-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/ignition-tools.pc
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/ignition-tools.README
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/ignition-tools/README.md

